  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dda \u0daf\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd4\u0da9\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Crazy drug addicts are now in the struggle",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister Prasanna Ranatunga, the chief organizer of the ruling party, said in Parliament today (27) that there are now only a group of madmen and drug dealers in the struggle ground.",
        "He said this during the debate on the announcement of the Emergency Law.",
        "He questioned a group of people who had signed the ancient photographs in the President's House, what kind of liberation is there for this country.",
        "Mr. Ranatunga said that the people of this country, which is affected by the economic problem, joined the struggle wholeheartedly, but they never expected uncivil behavior from the strugglers and that the people are now tired of the struggle due to the crazy work of the strugglers.",
        "The chief organizer of the ruling party said that the militants treated the army and the police in a low manner and expressed his gratitude to the army and the police for their efforts to curb the violence that took place in the middle of the struggle.",
        "Mr. Prasanna Ranatunga said that a separate tribute should be paid to them.",
        "He further mentioned that the violence of the activists should be controlled somehow."
      ],
